The `AuthenticationManager` is a container for authentication providers, giving a consistent interface to them all.

Inorder to have AuthenticationManager bean to be in the spring context, you can use the following solution.

    @Bean
    public AuthenticationManager authenticationManager(AuthenticationConfiguration authenticationConfiguration) throws Exception {
         return authenticationConfiguration.getAuthenticationManager();
    }

And you can inject AuthenticationManager wherever you need.

